  "text": "The main source of vitamin D is endogenous production in the skin where ultraviolet B energy in the sunlight converts 7-dehydrocholestrol to cholecalciferol (vitamin D3) ( Figure 1 ). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Dietary contribution to vitamin D status includes foods such as egg yolk, beef liver, cod liver oil, fatty fish, fortified milk and milk products.",
